{"updated_at": "2012-03-27T20:24:26Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-03-27T20:24:26Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4725535", "id": 4725535, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5619", "issue_id": 5619, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/jcoleman", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "d8d5058aa91cd439f1f486f93f8eb564", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/d8d5058aa91cd439f1f486f93f8eb564?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F518fe206be008d8f98488ba515188a69.png", "id": 125331, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/events{/privacy}", "login": "jcoleman", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcoleman/followers"}, "body": "This adds a hash lookup to each tag generated (which some have objected to) but I've run some benchmarks:\r\n\r\n    require 'benchmark'\r\n\r\n    h = {:a => 1}\r\n\r\n    Benchmark.bm(10) do |x|\r\n      x.report('empty loop'){ 10000000.times { nil  } }\r\n      x.report('hash lookup'){ 10000000.times { h[:a]  } }\r\n    end\r\n\r\nAnd found that Ruby (on my not so fast MacBook) can do 10 million hash lookups in under half a second. So I don't think this causes any performance problems.", "_id": {"$oid": "5238151dbd3543c15100dca1"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5619#issuecomment-4725535"}
